displayName: Capital Fotizona, Archaeologist Parryo's Research Laboratory

parameters:
Archaeologist Paryo: I can't stand it if valuable items get
damaged, so please leave.

Clea: I came to deliver the coin that we received as a
request from the Adventurer's Guild in Ftera.

Archaeologist Paryo: I would like to see that coin in more
detail...

Archaeologist Paryo: I don't doubt the Adventurer's Guild,
but there are many adventurers who bring fake items when
they hear that I am collecting. I would like to examine it.

Archaeologist Paryo: This is...! Without a doubt, it's
authentic. As expected of the Adventurer's Guild!
Storge of Love: I also want to be praised like that.
Clea: Storge-san, why are you here?

Storge of Love: I was the one doing this job. Lately, I've
been doing more office work and haven't been able to collect
as much as before.

Storge of Love: In that case... I want to appoint Clea as
my successor.
Clea: Is it okay if it's me?

Archaeologist Paryo: Delivering a single coin to me, who
knows that this job is not as easy as you think, is proof of
your ability.

Archaeologist Paryo: I don't mind. It seems like these
girls are better than you, Storge, who's always cooped up.

Storge of Love: Since you'll be adventuring all over the
empire with permission from the client, could you also look
for it while you're at it?

Storge of Love: Well then, I'll go back to my room to
hibernate.
古代のコインチュートリアル脱出
古代のコインチュートリアル脱出
古代のコインチュートリアル脱出

Archaeologist Paryo: I think you already know, but I
collect these ancient coins.

Archaeologist Paryo: I collect various things related to
the history of the empire, not just ancient coins, you
know.
Thief Nora: Indeed, that's an impressive amount!

Archaeologist Paryo: I want you to continue collecting
coins.

Archaeologist Paryo: As for the reward... how about
exchanging it for the coins and collectibles I've gathered?

Archaeologist Paryo: These are valuable things that you
can't buy at just any store. I think they will surely be
useful in your adventures, don't you think?
Clea: Understood. I'll continue to do my best.

Archaeologist Paryo: Negotiations are complete! When you
gather the coins, come talk to me.
実績 古代への情熱

Archaeologist Paryo: You can only own 99 ancient coins, so
I recommend exchanging them frequently here.

Archaeologist Paryo: I can't believe you're exchanging all
the prizes...!

Archaeologist Paryo: Actually, I've discovered that even
though the collected coins may look similar, there are
subtle differences.
Archaeologist Paryo: This is also thanks to all of you.

Archaeologist Paryo: As a token of gratitude, I will give
you my treasured items. They should be useful for your
challenging adventures.
Clea: I will use them carefully.

Archaeologist Paryo: If you find any ancient coins, I'll
buy them from you.
Archaeologist Paryo: Please come talk to me.

parameters:
Assistant Litrone: Teacher may be strict, but I'm really
happy to be able to help with the research.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Assistant Litrone: Teacher, you seem busy... Is something
wrong?

Assistant Litrone: Magic mirror... Could it be?! The Magic
Mirror!?

Assistant Litrone: The so-called MM, created by an ancient
civilization--

Assistant Litrone: The legendary creation of the ancient
Esordi civilization...

Archaeologist Paryo: Wait! I don't know what the request
is, but refuse it immediately!

Archaeologist Paryo: The Magic Mirror is a terrifying
creation made to expose captured slaves and criminals...

Archaeologist Paryo: What do you intend to use such a
torture device for?!
Clea: Why would you desire something like that...?

Thief Nora: Hmm... Maybe you're misunderstanding
something?
Clea: Yes, let's go to Mr. Fal's place and confirm it.
イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Assistant Litrone: Teacher may be strict, but I'm really
happy to be able to help with the research.

Archaeologist Paryo: It seems that I have put you all in
danger with such a thing happening.
Priestess Sophia: All's well that ends well, I suppose.

Archaeologist Paryo: You all are truly strong. I am amazed
by your mental strength.
Archaeologist Paryo: This is the promised reward.

Archaeologist Paryo: Your efforts and rewards are not
proportional. If it's alright with you, would you be willing
to use it for your adventures?

Archaeologist Paryo: Don't worry, this is something that
bears the name of the goddess.
Priestess Sophia: Oh my, thank you very much.

Archaeologist Paryo: I don't worship any specific
goddess... but I hope that you all receive the blessings of
the goddess Imiserinos.
